The Port Authority of New York and NewJersey said it has awarded USX Corp a 3,400,000 dlr contract toreplace the expansion joints and gratings on the upper level ofthe George Washington Bridge between New York and Fort Lee,N.J.    It said most of the joints and gratings have been in placefor over 50 years.  The bridge opened in 1931    Work on the project should start this spring and becompleted in the fall of 1988, it said.  Work affecting trafficwill be performed on weeknights and at least one lane in eachdirection will remain open at all times. Reuter&#3;